[THINKING]:  The issue is that my test was expecting the F rule to be applied in the same iteration as the X rule expansion. But actually, looking at the implementation, it does a single pass over the current string - replacing characters according to rules. So if we start with "X", and we have rules X -> F[+X]F[-X] and F -> FF, then:
- In iteration 1: "X" -> "F[+X]F[-X]" (each X replaced, F is not in the source yet)
- In iteration 2: Each F becomes FF and the X inside becomes F[+X]F[-X
